Lets do some cleaning here

library(stringr)
corpus <- tm_map(corpus, tolower)
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(corpus, tolower): transformation drops documents
#inspect(corpus[1:5])

corpus <- tm_map(corpus,removePunctuation)
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(corpus, removePunctuation): transformation drops
## documents
corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeNumbers)
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(corpus, removeNumbers): transformation drops
## documents
#inspect(corpus[1:5])

cleanset <- tm_map(corpus, removeWords,stopwords("en"))
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(corpus, removeWords, stopwords("en")):
## transformation drops documents
removeURL <- function(x)gsub('http[[:alnum:]]*','',x)

cleanset <- tm_map(cleanset,content_transformer(removeURL))
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(cleanset, content_transformer(removeURL)):
## transformation drops documents
cleanset_final <- gsub("<NA>","",cleanset)
cleanset <- tm_map(cleanset, stripWhitespace)
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(cleanset, stripWhitespace): transformation drops
## documents
#inspect(cleanset[1:5])
tdm <- TermDocumentMatrix(cleanset)

tdm <- as.matrix(tdm)

#tdm[1:10,1:10]

Removing shib, shibainu,shibarmy,shibs from the data

cleanset <- tm_map(cleanset, removeWords,c("shib","shibainu","shibs","shibarmy"))
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(cleanset, removeWords, c("shib", "shibainu", :
## transformation drops documents
tdm <- TermDocumentMatrix(cleanset)

tdm <- as.matrix(tdm)

Lets make bar plot of the tdm

w <- rowSums(tdm)

Now create a subset , of w

w <- subset(w,w>10)

# From the above graph we can see that words like cryptobeast,crypto,hashtags,urt,ubufef,now are not useful for the analysis, so lets remove these words as well

cleanset <- tm_map(cleanset, removeWords,c("cryptobeast","crypto","hashtags","urt","now"))
## Warning in tm_map.SimpleCorpus(cleanset, removeWords, c("cryptobeast",
## "crypto", : transformation drops documents

# Lets make wordcloud with the help of libraries wordcloud and wordcloud2

library(wordcloud)
## Loading required package: RColorBrewer
w <- sort(rowSums(tdm),decreasing = TRUE)

wordcloud(words = names(w),
          freq = w)
## Warning in wordcloud(words = names(w), freq = w): mentioned could not be fit on
## page. It will not be plotted.
## Warning in wordcloud(words = names(w), freq = w): follow could not be fit on
## page. It will not be plotted.

# Biggest word shows frequency of these words are more in the data , we can make some changes in word cloud with the help of following code :

wordcloud(words = names(w),
          freq = w,
          max.words = 150,

We can use wordcloud2 to make more fancy wordcloud :

library(wordcloud2)
## Warning: package 'wordcloud2' was built under R version 4.1.2
w <- data.frame(names(w),w)

#w
colnames(w)<- c('word','freq')
#w

wordcloud2(w,
           size = 0.8,
           shape = 'circle')
wordcloud2(w,
           size = 0.6,
           shape = 'star')
wordcloud2(w,
           size = 0.5,
           shape = 'star',
           rotateRatio = 0.5,
           minSize = 1)
